cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the problem of detecting out-of-distribution samples in deep learning models, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing methods and proposes a new evaluation scheme, which involves evaluating on three datasets instead of two. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deal with issues related to security and optimization in machine learning models.
